    • Constructor Detail

      • StudentList

        public StudentList()
        The constructor initializes the array that will store all of the students. It is initialized at array size 10. It also intializes the totalStudents to 0.

    • Method Detail

      • add

        public void add​(Student s)
        This method adds a student into the list. If list is full, it calls grow() add more space to the list.
        Parameters:
        s - is the student that will be added into the list.

      • remove

        public void remove​(Student s)
        This method removes a student from the list. It calls the findStudent() method to find the index of the student that should be removed. If the student is not found, the method returns without doing anything. When the student is found, it removes that student and shifts every student to the right of it over one space.
        Parameters:
        s - is the student that will be removed from the list.

      • print

        public void print()
        This method prints each student in the list with their tuition due.

      • contains

        public boolean contains​(Student s)
        This method checks if a student exists in the list.
        Parameters:
        s - is the student being searched for.
        Returns:
        true if the student is within the list and false if the student is not in the list.

      • isEmpty

        public boolean isEmpty()
        This method checks if the list is empty.
        Returns:
        true if empty and false if not.
